---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
---

<Base title="Frameworks">
  <article>
    <h1>Frameworks</h1>
    <p class="subtitle" style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
      Thinking tools for daily decisions
    </p>

    <h2>Core Operating Model</h2>

    <div class="card-grid full-width">
      <Card title="Behavioral Activation" status="active" tags={["psychology", "core"]} href="/frameworks/behavioral-activation">
        <p>The operating model: action produces motivation. From CBT research, applied to solopreneur operations.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Infinite Sales Cycle" status="active" tags={["sales"]} href="/frameworks/infinite-sales-cycle">
        <p>Create &rarr; Publish &rarr; Engage &rarr; Convert &rarr; Deliver &rarr; Document &rarr; Create. The cycle never stops.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="5-Minute Wins" status="active" tags={["daily-ops"]} href="/frameworks/five-minute-wins">
        <p>Catalog of quick actions by category: visibility, engagement, content, sales.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Content Leverage" status="active" tags={["content"]} href="/frameworks/content-leverage">
        <p>1 lab session &rarr; 7+ content pieces. Never create for one platform only.</p>
      </Card>
    </div>

    <h2>Agent Workflows</h2>

    <div class="card-grid full-width">
      <Card title="5-Level Autonomy" status="active" tags={["agents", "architecture"]}>
        <p>From Copilot to Observer. How to gradually increase agent independence as trust builds.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Inner / Outer Loop" status="active" tags={["agents", "workflow"]}>
        <p>What you do (review, decide, ship) vs. what agents do (research, draft, monitor). The boundary that defines your OS.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Trust Calibration" status="active" tags={["agents", "decision-making"]}>
        <p>When to trust agent output and when not to. 5-stage maturity model from Skeptic to Orchestrator.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="MCP for Solopreneurs" status="active" tags={["mcp", "tools"]}>
        <p>Model Context Protocol &mdash; how agents connect to Obsidian, LinkedIn, Telegram, and 10,000+ other tools.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="CLAUDE.md Pattern" status="active" tags={["context", "how-to"]}>
        <p>One file that makes every agent interaction 10x better. Persistent memory across sessions.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Skills Architecture" status="active" tags={["skills", "reusable"]}>
        <p>Reusable agent behaviors. Build once, invoke forever. 50+ skills as lead magnets.</p>
      </Card>
    </div>

    <h2>LinkedIn &amp; Sales</h2>

    <div class="card-grid full-width">
      <Card title="LinkedIn Interest Graph" status="active" tags={["linkedin", "algorithm"]}>
        <p>2026 shift: posts reach people by topic, not connection. Consistency beats virality.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="LinkedIn Hook Patterns" status="active" tags={["linkedin", "writing"]}>
        <p>5 proven hook templates for AI educators. The first 2 lines determine everything.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="LinkedIn Content Calendar" status="active" tags={["linkedin", "schedule"]}>
        <p>1.5&ndash;2 hours/week. 3 posts. Teaching, proof, conversation. No heroics.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Dual Language Strategy" status="active" tags={["international"]}>
        <p>One language per platform. LinkedIn = English. Telegram = Russian. Don't dilute.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Alumni as Marketing Engine" status="active" tags={["sales", "community"]}>
        <p>350+ alumni are your best sales team. Certificate shares, referrals, word of mouth.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="JTBD for Sales" status="active" tags={["jtbd", "positioning"]}>
        <p>Your customers don't buy a lab. They hire it to do a job. Switch forces as sales framework.</p>
      </Card>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
